com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions.specialized

Interface BiPredicate<A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the first argument type
    B - the second argument type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<Fn1<B,Boolean>,Fn1<A,?>>, BiPredicate<A,B>, Fn1<A,Fn1<B,Boolean>>, Fn2<A,B,Boolean>, Function<A,Fn1<B,Boolean>>, Functor<Fn1<B,Boolean>,Fn1<A,?>>, Profunctor<A,Fn1<B,Boolean>,Fn1>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface BiPredicate<A,B>
extends Fn2<A,B,Boolean>, BiPredicate<A,B>
    A specialized Fn2 that returns a Boolean when fully applied, or a Predicate when partially applied.
